    ],
    "summary": "On 22 November 2023 at approximately 1125 hours, a contract construction worker with Burner Fire Control was guiding an eight-foot section of two-inch diameter airline piping being lowered from an elevated pipe rack to the lower deck via rope on Cox Operating's Mobile 916 Platform AP. During the lowering operation, the pipe shifted causing the injured person's right index finger to be pinched between the piping and an I-beam support. The worker was wearing leather impact gloves at the time. The IP was evacuated and diagnosed with a fractured right index finger, resulting in a Loss Time Accident of greater than three days (4-6 weeks recovery).",
    "recommendations": [
      "No recommendations issued by BSEE New Orleans District"
    ],
    "key_phrases": [
      "inadequate communication between personnel",
      "no or inadequate supervision",
      "pipe shifted",
      "finger pinched between piping and beam",
      "Loss Time Accident greater than three days"
    ]
  },
